Company Overview
As of October 23, 2006, Safety Components International, Inc. was acquired by International Textile Group, Inc. in a reverse merger transaction. International Textile Group, Inc. manufactures and markets soft goods for apparel and automotive airbag fabrics, automotive airbag cushions, government uniforms, commission finishing, interior furnishings, and development stage activities. Its products portfolio comprises automotive safety products, including airbag fabric and airbag cushions; bottom-weight woven apparel fabrics, such as denim, synthetic, and worsted fabrics; government uniform fabrics that include fabrics for military dress uniforms and battle dress uniforms; interior furnishings f...
As of October 23, 2006, Safety Components International, Inc. was acquired by International Textile Group, Inc. in a reverse merger transaction. International Textile Group, Inc. manufactures and markets soft goods for apparel and automotive airbag fabrics, automotive airbag cushions, government uniforms, commission finishing, interior furnishings, and development stage activities. Its products portfolio comprises automotive safety products, including airbag fabric and airbag cushions; bottom-weight woven apparel fabrics, such as denim, synthetic, and worsted fabrics; government uniform fabrics that include fabrics for military dress uniforms and battle dress uniforms; interior furnishings fabrics; and specialty fabrics and services, which include commission printing and finishing, and value added technical fabrics used in various industrial and commercial applications. International Textile Group serves automotive, apparel, government fabric, and interior furnishings markets in North America, Europe, South Africa, and China. The company was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Greensboro, North Carolina.
